  <sections xmi:id="_CBlEEPsnEeiOY5TxRmxENA" name="Build the core of the team" guid="_CBlEEPsnEeiOY5TxRmxENA">
    <sectionDescription>A project of the type that will use Crystal Clear often starts with an Executive Sponsor and a Lead Designer, and&#xD;
eventually a key user. Normally, two to five other people are added to the project, with a various mix of skills,&#xD;
experience and ability</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_ETli8PsnEeiOY5TxRmxENA" name="Perform the Exploratory 360° " guid="_ETli8PsnEeiOY5TxRmxENA">
    <sectionDescription>At an early point in the project, the team – including the executive sponsor – does a once-around check of the key&#xD;
issues.&amp;nbsp; In this check, they make sure the project won't founder on the business value, the requirements, the domain&#xD;
model, the technology to be used, the project plan, the team makeup, or the methodology or conventions to be used.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_HkeE4PsnEeiOY5TxRmxENA" name="Shape and fine-tune the methodology conventions" guid="_HkeE4PsnEeiOY5TxRmxENA">
    <sectionDescription>A&amp;nbsp;methodology is nothing more than the conventions the team agrees to adopt. Since the set of conventions will be&#xD;
revisited twice per iteration or delivery cycle, it would, in principle be possible to start from any methodology and&#xD;
simply tune it over time to suit the team.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_Ifqh0PsnEeiOY5TxRmxENA" name="Build the initial project plan" guid="_Ifqh0PsnEeiOY5TxRmxENA">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Techniques that provides an initial project plan, and is fast enough that it can be used on a regular basis to track&#xD;
    changes in the project's situation and make an updated project plan.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
In this project we're using&amp;nbsp;&quot;Blitz Planning&quot; (described on work products)&lt;br /></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
